 Sab <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucorae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 1:26:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.immortalvision.com/images/MemberPics/corae_60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game *move to equip</span><hr size=1> Corae Bearfeet, halfing druid here.  I maxed out wisdom and I am very glad I did.  At level 57, I could easily get over 200 wis with the gear I've gotten, but more and more I find myself running around with about 180 - I'm addicted to clickables and most of them don't have any wis - Fungi tunic, ES arms, gloves, bracer, lumi staff...  I can solo Giant Elites without using one ounce of mana if I have to.  As far as stamina goes, yea I suppose its good, but I can't think of one instance where a few more hps would have saved my life.  I can think of many, many times where I wish I had enough mana for one more snare (pre-gloves of course ;)  <p><p style="line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Viner Hand ITC" size="3">Corae
