</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueyeds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyeds</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 3:46:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game *move to equip</span><hr size=1> Yes I did give close to the best highest wis in each slot, close but not the best.  But please look back and notice that I only put in 9 slots.  There is also the face the rings, earings, boots, shield slot (If lod is on your back as mine is) Arms, head, even the legs I put in the HIGH ac legs not the high wis legs.  Othmir totem and Lod shield are the only hard ones to obtain here.<br>
 <p>Eyed
57 Druid
Proud member of Inner Fire
Lanys</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 5:56:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game *move to equip</span><hr size=1> I maintain that it is better to put the points in wisdom at the front end and &quot;remove&quot; them by taking off +wisdom items at the back end.  The overall benefit to the high end player is greater.<br>
<br>
The basic point about wisdom at the high end is correct.  Even as a 110 wisdom druid, I can now get over 230 wisdom with the fairly standard +wis equipment of any raid-capable druid.  Obviously, I don't need all that wisdom, and have made many tradeoffs for higher AC, HP and resist items.  None of my jewelry has wisdom, for example.  Nor do my boots or sleeves.  In each case, I have gone for the best high AC, high HP, high resist item combination I could obtain.<br>
<br>
There are two ways to do the trade-off.  First, you can lower your wisdom at the front end by 5 or 10 points, and put those points elsewhere.    If you put then in Agility, the most you will see is a 1 to 3 point boost in AC, right?  If you put them in Stamina, you will see approximately 25 to 30 additional hp, right?  These benefits are relatively minor, compared to the AC and HP equipment that you will have to give up at the higher levels to maintain your wisdom at 200.  You also have lower wisdom throughout your lower levels, if that is a concern.<br>
<br>
Second, you can max out your base wisdom and give up wisdom in the form of +wis items later.  It gives you greater flexibility at the higher levels to swap in equipment that gives you much better boosts to AC, HP and resists than those 5 to 10 points do at the front end.  If you are just barely breaking 200 at 60, you are limiting your equipment options (assuming you want to maintain 200).<br>
<br>
Why give up 7 wisdom points at the front end and force yourself to wear a +7 wisdom ring at 60, when you could have put those points in wis at the beginning, and swap out that +7 wis ring for a 9th step coldain ring, with 9 AC, magic resistance, and nice HP.   The benefits of that single item outshine any benefit you would see from those 7 initial points invested in some stat other than wisdom.<br>
<br>
Why is this?  Any shaman can tell you.  With a few exceptions, modest changes in stats don't have a significant impact in the game.  And that's why adding 5 or 10 points to str, sta, or agility at the front end ultimately is meaningless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 7:17:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game *move to equip</span><hr size=1> Well.. It might be the case that with the really top end gear you end up with too much wisdom. <br>
