<br>
Not picking on anyone here - but this is a very untrue statement. I am 230 wis, I started at under 100 wis and put the rest into stamina/agi. During my younger years this hurt a lot - we didn't have Kunark and Velious. I was told at the time that I should just start over and put all my points into Wis and then stam or agi (dodge factor) (should of been a halfling, sneak owns). Many times I felt like doing this because it was so hard to keep 200 wis. But then I started asking other 50 druids about there HPs - they seem to be dying a lot faster then me and having not used all there mana. This was during the old Vox and Naggy Raids, I didn't see it then.. but then Kunark came out.. more items with more Wis.. wow I have more wis then I need.. so I started putting it into stam (mod rods are great).. Again druids would fall during Trak Fights and VP - I would be standing there getting in the final Shot to kill Trak or Silverwing and they be dead. Then I saw it.. I had more hps, more Agi and the same amount of Wis.. why? It was the lack of Stam/Wis or Stam/AC or HP/Wis items out during Kunark (exception: Epic 15 stam +10 hps + mana + 20 Wis ). <br>
<br>
Now we have Velious, Stam, HP, Wis, Str galore.. multiple items have the stats I like.. and with my higher Stam and Agi, and lower Wis.. My Hps keep going up and AC is nice.<br>
<br>
<u>This is Walk around Gear</u><br>
Hard AC: 253 (Hard AC = Base, not Worn AC)<br>
Extra Mana: 775<br>
Extra Hps + stam: 842 ( stam 1 point = 3 points )<br>
Wis: 230<br>
Stam Calculation: 25 Stam off the Ayill's Aged Stone Shield = 75 hps.<br>
<br>
I can now go more HPs, or More Mana, depending on the Mob. <br>
<br>
Lots ask me why I have this or that gear: <br>
<br>
Well some mobs drain mana, not hps.<br>
Vice Some Mobs drain hps, while I am draining mana.<br>
AC isn't useless, though I can buff to 1100 ac, whats the point? I am a raid druid. <br>
<br>
Best thing to do IMO is if an item has a huge concentration of a stat that you use, get it!<br>
<br>
Othmir Totem: Stam and Wis<br>
Resist Stones: Minor Stats, Big Resist.<br>
<br>
Also I suggest perm items, things you don't need to take off when changing out gear.<br>
<br>
IE: Belt of Dwarf Slaying, (exception of the neg cha) CT's Eye and Brain, Gauntlets of Dragon Slaying. <br>
<br>
Woven Grass Arms I haven't changed out in a while.<br>
<br>
I change out bracers, rings, earrings, face, head piece, shoulders, boots, pants, bp, neck.. hmm is there anything else?<br>
<br>
An 8-inventory slot with Bags gives you a lot of space and I use them.<br>
<br>
This is me,  it works for me, for I am a raid druid nothing more.<br>
